Garbage collect orphaned dependencies that are no longer used by any branch.

This command:
1. Scans all worktrees to identify which dependencies are in use
2. Finds dependencies that are no longer referenced by any branch
3. Calculates the total space that can be reclaimed
4. Optionally deletes orphaned dependencies to free up disk space

Use --dry-run to preview what would be deleted without actually deleting.
Use --force to skip the confirmation prompt.

Usage:
  git-hop env gc [flags]

Aliases:
  gc, cleanup, clean

Flags:
      --dry-run   Show what would be deleted without deleting
      --force     Skip confirmation prompt
  -h, --help      help for gc

Global Flags:
      --config string   config file (default is $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/git-hop/config.json)
      --format string   Output format (table, json, yaml) (default "table")
  -g, --global          use global hopspace in $GIT_HOP_DATA_HOME (default: local)
      --json            output in JSON format
      --no-color        Disable ANSI colour
      --no-hints        Suppress next-step hints after command output
      --porcelain       machine-readable output
  -q, --quiet           Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose         verbose output
